						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a perpetual lamp in the temple to be maintained by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tirutturutti, by <hi rend="bold">Muḷḷūr-Naṅgaiyār the mother of the Chōḷa queen</hi> (Sōḻamādēviyār) the consort of Parakēsarivarman. This donor is already known from Nos. 45 and 125 of 1895 (See Instroduction.)</p>						

